Can 'summary' be added as an accepted field to the jira.view.issue.links.sort.order property?

 

Quote from Jira [documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver/configuring-issue-linking-938847862.html]:
{code:java}
Jira system administrators can define the order in which linked issues are displayed in the Issue Links section on the 'view issue' page. This is done by editing the value of the jira.view.issue.links.sort.order property on Jira's Advanced settings page. The jira.view.issue.links.sort.order property can accept the following individual field values: 'key', 'type', 'status', 'priority' and 'resolution'.{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-41876].
  {panel}

Currently, there is no limit in sending REST API request. In some cases where users sending REST API request to run complex JQL queries with high frequency, it returns enormous number of results and it potentially causes an outage for the instance. 

To prevent it to happen, it would be great if there is a limit on REST API requests.
